Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Tajikistan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung", a famous work of leader Kim Jong Il, was brought out in booklet by a newspaper office of Tajikistan. 
 The work, made public on October 2, Juche 84 (1995), is the undying great programme of the party building and activities which proudly summed up the glorious history of the Workers' Party of Korea that pioneered a new road for the building of a revolutionary party in the era of independence under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and clarified the way of strengthening the WPK into the party of the President forever. 
 A releasing ceremony took place on Oct. 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shabdolov, chairman of the Communist Party of Tajikistan, said at the ceremony that it is of weighty significance to publish the famous work of Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 T. B. Karimov, organizational secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Tajikistan, said that the WPK is a dignified party and a party which has taken deep roots among the popular masses. We should certainly know the history and experience of the struggle of the WPK and become the fighters for rebuilding genuine socialism, he noted, and went on: The WPK and socialist Korea are now respected and yearned by the world progressive humankind. We will invariably keep faith in socialism at all times.

WPK Praised by Polish and Indian Political Figures 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- Political figures of Poland and India issued statements on Oct. 5 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea, at which they praised the WPK as a powerful party. 
 Martin Adam, chairman of the National Executive Committee of the Polish Communist Party, in a statement said that to grandly celebrate the 60th anniversary of the WPK founded by sagacious President Kim Il Sung is a clear demonstration of the farsighted leadership of the WPK struggling for the wellbeing of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the WPK is pushing ahead with the cause of socialist construction while shattering the U.S. imperialists' moves of aggression step by step under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, the successor to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 G. Debarajan, secretary of the Central Committee of the All-India Forward Bloc, in a statement said that over the last 60 years since its foundation the WPK has covered the proud road, recording victory and glory in the annals of history despite the repeated difficulties and ordeals. 
 Today the WPK has been strengthened into a powerful party which achieved the single-minded unity of the leader, the party and the masses and powerfully organized and led the Korean people in their struggle for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and the accomplishment of the cause of national reunification under the outstanding and tested leadership of Kim Jong Il, he added.

Normalization of Japan-DPRK Diplomatic Relations Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- Isamu Shimizu, chairman of the Nagano, Japan, Prefectural People's Council for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, was interviewed by KCNA on Oct. 11 after participating in  celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. He said he will launch a powerful campaign for the reunification of Korea and the normalization of the Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations.
 He noted he was deeply moved to see the army and people of the DPRK out for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, single-mindedly rallied around General Secretary Kim Jong Il, true to the behests of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 2005 is marking the 60th anniversary of the defeat of Japanese imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world attention is now focused on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The denuclearization of the peninsula and the normalization of the DPRK-U.S. and Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations are important matters for the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea and for detente and peaceful co-existence in Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is registering many successes in the settlement of these matters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of Korea's reunification has now become historic inevitability no one can arrest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The door for normalizing Japan-DPRK diplomatic ties is open thanks to the historic Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration but this issue is undergoing ordeals due to the reactionary forces of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will further strengthen the movement for the normalization of Japan-DPRK diplomatic ties as well as the activities for supporting the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will also wage positive struggle to defend the national rights of the Koreans in Japan against the moves to distort history textbooks, bid for permanent membership of the UNSC and official visit to the Yasukuni Shrine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will launch a dynamic campaign to make the Japanese government honestly implement the Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration, apologize and compensate for the past colonial rule over Korea and withdraw its hostile policy toward the DPRK.

Anti-U.S., Anti-War Meeting Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- A Seoul regional meeting for the implementation of the joint statement of the six-party talks and the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea was held on Oct. 8, according to a press report.
 Present there were members of civic and public organizations including the Seoul Reunification Solidarity and the Seoul People's Solidarity and youth and students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the meeting said that they would conduct an all-out action against the United States not willing to sincerely implement the joint statement adopted at the fourth round of the six-party talks and take the lead in the struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces.
 Similar meetings took place in Taegu, Kwangju, Phyongthaek and other places on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the meeting, youth and students under the Seoul District Federation of University Student Councils and the June 15 Youth and Students Solidarity staged a grand Seoul regional march for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces.

Rodong Sinmun on U.S. Senate's Decision to Cut down Cost for Research of Smaller Nukes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Senate Appropriations Committee decided to deduct a total amount of 4.5 million US dollars, expenses for the research of smaller nukes, from the appropriations for the fiscal year 2006, which has put a brake on the U.S. administration's moves for military expansion to complete the development of nuclear weapons of practical use for smashing anti-U.S. independent countries, says Rodong Sinmun Thursday in a signed commentary.
 The deduction of a total expense for the research of smaller nukes deals a heavy blow to the neo-conservative forces of the U.S. in their attempt to pressurize those countries incurring their displeasure with nuclear weapons, the commentary notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bringing to light the reason why the U.S. Senate had no choice but to make such a decision, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military expenditure of the U.S. dreaming of world domination has snowballed in recent years close to 500 billion US dollars. This is a record high in the U.S. history. It is, therefore, as clear as noonday that the U.S. is not in a position to squander a large amount of money for the research of smaller nukes given that anti-war spirit is mounting within the U.S. day by day and the public is growing suspicious about the U.S. occupation of Iraq.
 The decision is also related to the big chaos caused by increased damage by hurricane that swept the country in late August. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result, the U.S. administration was compelled to stop developing the nukes because it found itself in a deplorable plight due to the tremendous expenses for Iraqi war and damage by hurricane Katrina. The U.S. bellicose forces were hit hard by it and have become limp.
 The recent U.S. Senate decision shows that the U.S. warlike forces' moves for a nuclear war cannot go ahead as they intend.
 But the U.S. ambition for nuclear weapons will remain unchanged.

Kim Yong Dae Meets Russian Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Dae, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, met and had a friendly talk with a delegation of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK led by  Chairman Vladimir Tolstikov at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. 
 On hand was Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairwoman of the Korea-Russia Friendship Association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion the head of the delegation he said he had an honor of attending the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea held here with splendid. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the position and influence of the DPRK are rising higher in the international arena under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il. He wished the Korean people greater success in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation.

Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 13 (KCNA) -- The Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia exhibition celebrating the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea successfully closed.
 At least 20,000 potted Kimilsungias and Kimjongilias were put on display by armed forces organs, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, the Cabinet Secretariat, the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Metal Industry, the Ministry of Forestry, the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission and other units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign friends, the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and other overseas Koreans exhibited immortal flowers.
 During the exhibition senior officials of the Party, the army and the state, members of the Cabinet, delegates to the celebrations of the 60th birthday of the WPK, officials of ministries and national institutions, over 200,000 servicepersons of the KPA, working people and school youth and children looked round the exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the visitors were the Chinese government delegation, the delegation of the Communist Party of Cuba and other foreign friends and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony took place at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Nung Su, chairman of the Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee, in a closing speech called upon all the participants to deepen a scientific study of the cultivation and propagation of immortal flowers so as to bring them into full bloom at home and working places and everywhere.
 Choe Thae Bok, Jong Ha Chol, Kwak Pom Gi and others were present at the closing ceremony.
